Hello Virginie,

The constructors were changed in this checkin:
https://webarchive.jira.com/source/changelog/HER?cs=7047

Using heritrix 3.1.0-RC1 or 3.1.0-SNAPSHOT you can approximate the old 
behavior of your program like so:

WARCWriterPoolSettings settings = new WARCWriterPoolSettingsData(prefix, 
WriterPoolMember.DEFAULT_TEMPLATE, 
WARCConstants.DEFAULT_MAX_WARC_FILE_SIZE, compressed, dirs, l, new 
UUIDGenerator());
WARCWriter writer = new WARCWriter(aint, settings);

One difference here is the use of a template for the warc filenames. If 
you need to maintain your existing naming convention, then you&#39;ll have 
to reconstruct the template and include your suffix in it. Then supply 
your template to the WARCWriterPoolSettingsData constructor instead of 
WriterPoolMember.DEFAULT_TEMPLATE.

There&#39;s some more information on that in the release notes:
https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/Release+Notes+-+Heritrix+3.1.0-RC1#ReleaseNotes-Heritrix3.1.0-RC1-NewformulaanddefaultconventionsforARC%2FWARCnamingtobetterguaranteeuniqueness%28HER1727%29

Noah


